# Media formats showcase

A tour of every slide type Reactable can render on the recorded stage.

deck do
  id: showcase
  title: Media Formats Showcase
end




client :showcase_title do
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;justify-content:center;padding:10vh 10vw;background:radial-gradient(ellipse 90% 70% at 15% -10%,rgba(99,102,241,.35),transparent 55%),radial-gradient(ellipse 50% 40% at 95% 90%,rgba(236,72,153,.15),transparent 50%),#050508;color:#fff;font-family:ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif;overflow:hidden">
    <div style="font:600 11px/1 ui-monospace,monospace;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#818cf8;margin-bottom:20px">Reactable · stage showcase</div>
    <h1 style="font-size:clamp(2.75rem,6vw,4.25rem);font-weight:650;letter-spacing:-.03em;line-height:1.05;margin:0 0 16px;max-width:14ch">Media formats</h1>
    <p style="font-size:clamp(1.1rem,2vw,1.5rem);color:#a1a1aa;margin:0 0 48px;max-width:28ch;line-height:1.4;font-weight:400">Everything you can drop into a recorded deck — prose, apps, embeds, and video.</p>
    <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px;margin-top:auto">
      <span style="font:500 12px ui-monospace,monospace;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(99,102,241,.18);border:1px solid rgba(129,140,248,.35);color:#c4b5fd">prose</span>
      <span style="font:500 12px ui-monospace,monospace;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(99,102,241,.18);border:1px solid rgba(129,140,248,.35);color:#c4b5fd">client</span>
      <span style="font:500 12px ui-monospace,monospace;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(99,102,241,.18);border:1px solid rgba(129,140,248,.35);color:#c4b5fd">iframe</span>
      <span style="font:500 12px ui-monospace,monospace;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(99,102,241,.18);border:1px solid rgba(129,140,248,.35);color:#c4b5fd">video</span>
      <span style="font:500 12px ui-monospace,monospace;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:999px;background:rgba(99,102,241,.18);border:1px solid rgba(129,140,248,.35);color:#c4b5fd">youtube</span>
    </div>
  </div>
end


## Prose slides

# Authored in `.work`

Speaker notes live in the slide header. Body text supports **emphasis**, lists, and `inline code` — rendered with deck typography before the stage loads.


client :pulse_slide do
  <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(165deg,#0c0c12,#151528 45%,#0a0a0f);color:#f2f2f2;font:16px/1.45 ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;padding:48px">
    <div style="max-width:520px;text-align:center">
      <div style="display:inline-block;font:600 10px ui-monospace,monospace;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#6ee7b7;padding:6px 12px;border-radius:8px;background:rgba(16,185,129,.12);border:1px solid rgba(16,185,129,.35);margin-bottom:24px">client :unit</div>
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:600;margin:0 0 12px;letter-spacing:-.02em">Custom HTML islands</h2>
      <p style="color:#9ca3af;margin:0 0 32px;line-height:1.55">Design title slides, diagrams, or UI mockups as reusable <code style="font:0.9em ui-monospace;color:#a5b4fc;background:rgba(99,102,241,.15);border:1px solid rgba(129,140,248,.3);padding:2px 8px;border-radius:5px">client :name</code> blocks in deck.work.</p>
      <div style="width:72px;height:72px;margin:0 auto;border-radius:50%;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#6366f1,#a855f7);box-shadow:0 0 60px rgba(99,102,241,.45);animation:pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite"></div>
    </div>
    <style>@keyframes pulse{0%,100%{transform:scale(1);opacity:1}50%{transform:scale(1.08);opacity:.9}}</style>
  </div>
end







# Ready to record

Press record on the bar — the rounded stage frame is exactly what lands in `stage.mov`.

1. Author slides in `deck.work`
2. Preview with **Stage** on the bar
3. Ship takes to HyperFrames or ffmpeg











